<figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="fig_1"><head>Figure 1 .</head><label>1</label><figDesc>Figure 1. SEM micrographs of (a) unbaked, and; (b) baked AgNI dot arrays samples. Scale bar equals to 500 nm; (c) particle size distribution on unbaked AgNI sample. &lt;d&gt; denotes the mean diameter, and σ is the standard deviation.; (d) A photograph of unbaked and baked AgNI samples.</figDesc><graphic coords="4,118.95,250.60,323.10,211.60" type="bitmap" /></figure>
<figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="fig_2"><head>Figure 2 .</head><label>2</label><figDesc>Figure 2. (a) UV-Vis reflectance spectra for baked and unbaked AgNI samples. Aa reflectance minimum at around 420 nm, which is due to LSPR of the Ag nanoparticles; (b) Raman spectrum of the bare PEN substrate and SERS spectra of BPY on unbaked and baked AgNI dot arrays.</figDesc></figure>
<figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="fig_3"><head>Figure 3 .</head><label>3</label><figDesc>Figure 3. (a) Batch-to-batch variation of the peak around 1610 cm -1 peak; (b) spot-to-spot variation and the standard deviation of the SERS measurements at different positions on the AgNI sample.</figDesc><graphic coords="6,88.25,260.40,406.80,160.10" type="bitmap" /></figure>
		</body>
